                   na_values=-200,usecols=use)

col_=df_air.columns.tolist()[2:]

for feature in col_:
    df_air[feature]=df_air[feature].fillna(df_air.groupby(['MONTH','HOUR'])[feature].transform('mean'))

Linear Regression

In[15]:
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler         #import normalisation package
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split      #import train test split
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression         #import linear regression package
from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error   #import mean squared error
In[16]:
X=df_air[col_].drop('RH',1)     #X-input features
y=df_air['RH']                    #y-input features
In[17]:
ss=StandardScaler()     #initiatilise
In[18]:
X_std=ss.fit_transform(X)     #apply stardardisation
In[19]:
#split the data into train and test with test size and 30% and train size as 70%
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test=train_test_split(X_std,y,test_size=0.3, random_state=42)

print('Training data size:',X_train.shape)
print('Test data size:',X_test.shape)

Training data size: (6549, 13)
Test data size: (2808, 13)
In[20]:
lr=LinearRegression()
lr_model=lr.fit(X_train,y_train)
In[21]:
print('Intercept:',lr_model.intercept_)
print('--------------------------------')
print('Slope:')
list(zip(X.columns.tolist(),lr_model.coef_))

Intercept: 49.292204302887775
--------------------------------
Slope:

In[22]:
y_pred_lr=lr_model.predict(X_test)                      #predict using the model
rmse_lr =np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test,y_pred_lr))      #calculate rmse
print('RMSE of Linear regression model:',rmse_lr)

RMSE of Linear regression model: 5.8216232887542825
In[23]:
y_test = np.array(y_test)
idx = np.argsort(y_test)

x = np.linspace(1, len(y_test), len(y_test))

plt.figure(figsize = (16, 10))
plt.title("Relative Humidity Regression", fontsize = 20)
plt.plot(x, y_pred_lr[idx],  '.',   alpha = 1,  label = 'Linear: {:.3f}'.format(rmse_lr))
plt.plot(x, y_test[idx], 'k-',  linewidth = 3, label = 'Actual Values')
plt.legend(loc = 4, fontsize = 15)
plt.ylabel("RH (%)", fontsize = 15)
plt.show()

Other Regression models

In[24]:
from sklearn.linear_model import Ridge
from sklearn.linear_model import Lasso
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsRegressor
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeRegressor  
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
In[25]:
ridge_reg = Ridge(alpha = 0.5)
lasso_reg = Lasso(alpha = 1)
knn_reg = KNeighborsRegressor(n_neighbors= 3)
dt_reg=DecisionTreeRegressor()
rf_reg=RandomForestRegressor()
In[26]:
ridge_model=ridge_reg.fit(X_train,y_train)
y_pred_ridge=ridge_model.predict(X_test) 
rmse_ridge =np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test,y_pred_ridge))
In[27]:
lasso_model=lasso_reg.fit(X_train,y_train)
y_pred_lasso=lasso_model.predict(X_test) 
rmse_lasso =np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test,y_pred_lasso))
In[28]:
knn_model=knn_reg.fit(X_train,y_train)
y_pred_knn=knn_model.predict(X_test) 
rmse_knn =np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test,y_pred_knn))
In[29]:
dt_model=dt_reg.fit(X_train,y_train)
y_pred_dt=dt_model.predict(X_test) 
rmse_dt =np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test,y_pred_dt))
In[30]:
rf_model=rf_reg.fit(X_train,y_train)
y_pred_rf=rf_model.predict(X_test) 
rmse_rf =np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test,y_pred_rf))
In[31]:
plt.figure(figsize = (16, 10))

x = np.linspace(1, len(y_test), len(y_test))

idx = np.argsort(y_test)

plt.title("Relative Humidity Regression", fontsize = 20)
plt.plot(x, y_pred_lr[idx],  '.',   alpha = 0.5,  label = 'LR: {:.3f}'.format(rmse_lr))
plt.plot(x, y_pred_ridge[idx],  '.',   alpha = 0.5,  label = 'Ridge: {:.3f}'.format(rmse_ridge))
plt.plot(x, y_pred_lasso[idx],  '.',   alpha = 0.5,  label = 'Lasso: {:.3f}'.format(rmse_lasso))
plt.plot(x, y_pred_knn[idx],  '.',   alpha = 0.5,  label = 'KNN: {:.3f}'.format(rmse_knn))
plt.plot(x, y_pred_dt[idx],  '.', alpha = 0.5,  label = 'DT: {:.3f}'.format(rmse_dt))
plt.plot(x, y_pred_rf[idx],  '.', alpha = 0.5, label = 'RF: {:.3f}'.format(rmse_rf))
plt.plot(x, y_test[idx], 'k-', linewidth = 2, label = 'Actual Values')
plt.legend(loc = 4, fontsize = 15)
plt.ylabel("RH (%)", fontsize = 15)
plt.grid(alpha = 0.3)
plt.show()
In[32]:
regs = ['LR', 'Ridge', 'Lasso', 'KNN',  'DT', 'RF']
rmses = [rmse_lr, rmse_ridge, rmse_lasso, rmse_knn, rmse_dt, rmse_rf]
y_preds = [y_pred_lr, y_pred_ridge, y_pred_lasso, y_pred_knn, y_pred_dt, y_pred_rf]
In[33]:
idx_ = np.argsort(rmses)

regs = np.asarray(regs)[idx_]
rmses = np.asarray(rmses)[idx_]
y_preds = np.asarray(y_preds)[idx_]

regs
Out[33]:
array(['RF', 'DT', 'KNN', 'Ridge', 'LR', 'Lasso'], dtype='<U5')
In[34]:
for i in range(len(regs)):
    plt.figure(figsize = (16, 10))
    plt.title("Relative Humidity Regression", fontsize = 20)
    for j in range(i+1):
        label = '{}: {:.3f}'.format(regs[-j-1], rmses[-j-1])
        if j == i:
             plt.plot(x, y_preds[-j-1][idx],  'r.',   alpha = 0.7,  label = label)
        else:
            plt.plot(x, y_preds[-j-1][idx],  '.',   alpha = 0.1,  label = label)
    plt.plot(x, y_test[idx], 'k-', linewidth = 2, label = 'Actual Values')
    plt.legend(loc = 4, fontsize = 15)
    plt.ylabel("RH (%)", fontsize = 15)
    plt.grid(alpha = 0.3)
    plt.show()
